$ System.Drawing.Bitmap (class)

`System.Drawing.Bitmap` encapsulates a GDI+ bitmap.

{ Creating a png with PowerShell

  The following simple example tries to demonstrate how a png can be created with → Windows/PowerShell. (By default, the `Save()` method of
 `System.Drawing.Bitmap` (which is implemented in the base class `System.Drawing.Image`) creates a png rather than a bmp!)
  gh|.NET-API|/System/Drawing/Bitmap/Hello-world.ps1||

  When executed, the script produces
  gh|.NET-API|/System/Drawing/Bitmap/img/Hello-world.png||

}

sa:
  An instance of `System.Drawing.Bitmap` is returned by the → Windows/PowerShell cmdLet → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/clipboard/get#get-clipboard-image[`get-image … -format image`].
